 a prolonged and fraught transition to democracy and eventual membership in the European Union. The young and educated have largely left. Governmental crisis and economic stagnation is the norm and much-needed regional cooperation has been suppressed by renewed nationalism. Wars on corruption have proved to be largely rhetorical. Making and Remaking the Balkans offers a systematic study of the issues the entire region faces as it struggles to complete the European integration process at a time when the European Union faces bigger problems elsewhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / European.2bisacsh  aBalkans.  aBosnia.  aCroatia.  aDemocracy.  aEuropean Integration.  aExpulsion.  aHistory.  aKosovo.  aPolitics.  aSerbia.  aState Capture.  aTransition.  aWar.  aYugoslavia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753071640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487530716423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487530716.jpg  a978-3-11-065206-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles